### Complete Symptom Picture

**Chief Symptoms:**
- Intermittent, colicky, or gnawing abdominal pain, often located around the umbilicus
- Sallow or pale-yellowish facial complexion, sometimes with small white spots
- Variable appetite, which may be ravenous (tapeworm) or poor
- Pica: desire to eat non-food items like dirt, clay, or uncooked rice (hookworm)
- Anal itching (pruritus ani), especially at night (pinworm)
- Grinding teeth at night (bruxism)

**Accompanying Symptoms:**
- Nausea, vomiting (may contain worms)
- Bad taste in mouth or bad breath
- Loose stools or alternating constipation and diarrhea
- Abdominal distension and bloating
- Cold limbs
- Fatigue and listlessness
- Visible worms or eggs in stool

