## âš ï¸ Contraindications & Cautions

**Treatment Contraindications:**
- Many antiparasitic herbs (e.g., Bing Lang, Ku Lian Pi) have some level of toxicity and are contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation.
- Use with extreme caution in patients who are very frail or have severe Qi and Blood Deficiency without concurrent tonifying herbs.

**Cautions:**
- Treatment should be followed by a course of Spleen-tonifying herbs to restore digestive health and prevent re-infestation.
- Hygiene is paramount: advise patients on hand washing, proper food preparation, and treating other household members if necessary.

