## ðŸ¥ Western Medical Correlates

**Common Western Diagnoses:**
- Helminthiasis (general term for worm infestation)
- Ascariasis (Roundworm)
- Enterobiasis (Pinworm)
- Cestodiasis (Tapeworm)
- Ancylostomiasis (Hookworm)

**Biomedical Understanding:**
This pattern directly corresponds to parasitic infections of the gastrointestinal tract. The TCM symptoms align well with biomedical understanding: parasites cause malabsorption and nutrient depletion (sallow complexion, deficiency), mechanical irritation and obstruction (abdominal pain), and specific allergic or toxic reactions (anal itching, pica).

