## ðŸ’¡ Clinical Pearls & Experience

### Clinical Tips
- Always inquire about teeth grinding, anal itching, and strange cravings, especially in children with digestive complaints.
- White spots on the face ("worm spots" or "tinea faciei") or nails can be a supporting sign.
- Treatment is often done in cycles (e.g., one week on, one week off) to target different stages of the parasite lifecycle.
- Consider treating the entire family to prevent re-infection, especially with pinworms.

### Common Mistakes
- Focusing only on expelling parasites without tonifying the underlying Spleen Deficiency. This can lead to recurrence.
- Using overly strong or toxic herbs for too long, which can damage the patient's Zheng Qi.

